{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Klasa","mdn_url":"/pl/docs/Glossary/Class","locale":"pl","native":"Polski","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>W <a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/OOP\">programowaniu obiektowym <small>(en-US)</small></a>&nbsp;<em>klasa </em>określa cechy&nbsp;<a href=\"/pl/docs/Glossary/Object\">obiektu</a>. Klasa definiuje&nbsp;<a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/property\">właściwości <small>(en-US)</small></a> i&nbsp;<a class=\"only-in-en-us\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/Method\">metody <small>(en-US)</small></a> obiektu, stanowi model, na podstawie którego tworzone są konkretne instancje klasy (obiekty).&nbsp;</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"dowiedz_się_więcej","title":"Dowiedz się więcej","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"wiedza_ogólna","title":"Wiedza ogólna","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Guide/Details_of_the_Object_Model#Class-based_vs._prototype-based_languages\">Języki programowania oparte na klasach vs języki oparte na prototypach</a>&nbsp;(np.&nbsp;JavaScript)</li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Introduction_to_Object-Oriented_JavaScript#The_Class\">Stosowanie funkcji jako klas w JavaScript</a></li>\n <li>(ang.)&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Class-based_programming\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Programowanie oparte na klasach</a>&nbsp;na Wikipedii</li>\n <li><a href=\"https://pl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Programowanie_obiektowe\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Programowanie obiektowe</a>&nbsp;na Wikipedii</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Dowiedz się więcej","id":"dowiedz_się_więcej"}],"summary":"W programowaniu obiektowym (en-US) klasa określa cechy obiektu. Klasa definiuje właściwości (en-US) i metody (en-US) obiektu, stanowi model, na podstawie którego tworzone są konkretne instancje klasy (obiekty).","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Klasse","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch"},{"title":"Class","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Clase","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Classe","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Class (クラス)","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"Class","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Класс","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Class（类）","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"Class（類）","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"pl/glossary/class","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/pl/glossary/class/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab41914e84897fea47d143","filename":"index.html"},"parents":[{"uri":"/pl/docs/Glossary","title":"Glossary"},{"uri":"/pl/docs/Glossary/Class","title":"Klasa"}],"pageTitle":"Klasa - Glossary | MDN","noIndexing":false}}